<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 6:00PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN MCKEAN COUNTY
THROUGH 630 PM EDT...
At 559 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles east of Kane, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Betula, Crosby, Kinzua Bridge State Park and Mount Jewett.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
north central Pennsylvania.</instruction>
